dcterms:creator: Uri Wilensky
dcterms:description: NetLogo is a widely used platform for agent-based modelling, allowing users to study complex group dynamics and simulate various phenomena.
dcterms:title: NetLogo

dcterms:creator: Uri Wilensky
dcterms:description: The NetLogo Wolf Sheep Predation Model simulates the interactions between wolves and sheep in an ecosystem, demonstrating predator-prey dynamics.
dcterms:title: NetLogo Wolf Sheep Predation Model

dcterms:creator: Uri Wilensky
dcterms:description: The NetLogo Flocking Model simulates the behavior of agents that move together in a flock, illustrating principles of collective behavior.
dcterms:title: NetLogo Flocking Model
